PIK3CA Variant Analysis via ctDNA 
I. PIK3CA variant analysis (0177U, 81309) via circulating tumor DNA (ctDNA) is 
considered medically necessary when: 
A. The member/enrollee has recurrent, unresectable, or stage IV hormone receptor-
positive/HER2-negative breast cancer, AND 
B. The member/enrollee is considering treatment with alpelisib plus fulvestrant, or 
capivasertib plus fulvestrant, AND 
C. The member/enrollee has had progression on at least one line of therapy.  
II. PIK3CA variant analysis (0177U, 81309) via circulating tumor DNA (ctDNA), is 
considered investigational for all other indications. 
