AR-V7 Circulating Tumor Cells (CTC) Analysis 
I. AR-V7  circulating tumor cells (CTC) analysis (81479) is considered medically 
necessary when: 
A. The member/enrollee has a diagnosis of metastatic castration-resistant prostate 
cancer, AND 
B. Tissue-based testing is not feasible for the member/enrollee, AND 
C. The test is ordered only once during the current cancer diagnosis, AND 
D. The member/enrollee has at least one of the following: 
1. Newly metastatic cancer, OR 
2. Signs of clinical, radiological or pathologic disease progression. 
